the splendid gift of not knowing with alice laplante the splendid gift of not knowing with alice laplante donald barthelme wrote it's appropriate to say that the writer is someone who confronted with a blank page does not know anything indeed one of the most difficult lessons a writer must learn is that uncertainty sometimes quite painful uncertainty is an integral part of the writing process it does not go away with age experience or praise alice laplante author of the making of a story a norton guide to creative writing will reveal how she's turned doubt from writer's block into one of the most exciting stages of her writing and how other writers can use it to generate truly fresh and urgent creative work alice laplante former stegner fellow and jones lecturer alice laplante has been teaching in the continuing studies program for more than fifteen years she is on the creative writing faculty at san francisco state university and has published short stories in southwest review epoch stanford magazine and other literary journals her book the making of a story a norton guide to creative writing was published in august 2007 date and time thursday january 24 2008 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s location pigott hall building 260 room 113 map url http csp stanford edu course evt196 asp audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members category lectures readings sponsor continuing studies contact 725 2650 continuingstudies stanford edu admission free and open to public download add to personal calendar vcal record email event print use this permalink last modified january 14 2008
